arm_group.arm_group_label: People who have dropped out of school

brief_summary.textblock:
The purpose of this study is to examine differences in selected psychiatric/psychological
      variables between a sample of unemployed young adults who have dropped out of high school
      and a sample of college students.

clinical_study.brief_title: Mental Health and Resilience in Emerging Adulthood

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Subjects 18-25 years old who have dropped out of school and who are currently
             unemployed

        Exclusion Criteria:

        -

study_pop.textblock: Subjects 18-25 years old who have dropped out of school and who are currently unemployed

clinical_study.official_title: Mental Health and Resilience in Emerging Adulthood

oversight_info.authority: Norway:National Committee for Medical and Health Research Ethics

primary_outcome.description: Participants will be subject to an assessment with the MINI International Neuropsychiatric Interview, resulting in an overview of axis-1 psychiatric disorders in the sample.
primary_outcome.measure: Prevalence of axis-1 disorders in the sample.

required_header.download_date: ClinicalTrials.gov processed this data on June 04, 2014
required_header.link_text: Link to the current ClinicalTrials.gov record.

secondary_outcome.description: Participants will be subject to an assessment with the Structured Clinical Interview for the Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders, Fourth Edition, resulting in an overview of axis-2 psychiatric disorders in the sample.
secondary_outcome.measure: Prevalence of axis-2 disorders in the sample.

clinical_study.study_design: Observational Model: Case Control, Time Perspective: Prospective
